      "message": "To prevent possible issues with stack overflow, we can convert this recursion to an iteration by explicitly maintaining the intermediate results that would be on the call stack, using |includedFiles| as the \"to-do list\", roughly something like this:\n\nstd::vector\u003cstd::string\u003e includedFiles \u003d scanDirInternal(path);\n\nwhile (includedFiles.size() \u003e 0) {\n    const auto\u0026 path \u003d includedFiles.pop();\n    if (pathIsDirInternal(path)) {\n        std::vector\u003cstd::string\u003e moreFiles \u003d scanDirInternal(path);\n        includedFiles.insert(includedFiles.end(), moreFiles.start(), \n                             moreFiles.end());\n    } else if (pathIsFileInternal(path)) {\n        FileSize theSize;\n        if (pathFileSizeInternal(path, \u0026theSize)) {\n            totalSize +\u003d theSize;\n        }\n    }\n}",
